Justification for Mapping: Subfield $a is not used with any of the date of creation subfields.  I think its use would be limited to manifestation dates.
When $a=n, the dates are unknown; the value will be "uuuu"
Notes (Uncategorized): Do we want "uuuu" to carry over to the RDA? Or do we want to transform it to "unknown"? Put a note instead that says "Date unknown?" -MCM 2021-12-14

Justification for Mapping: When $a=p, date 2 is date of production/recording

Justification for Mapping: When $a=p, date 1 is date of distribution/release/issue

When $a=t, date 1 is the year of publication, release, production, or execution
Notes (Uncategorized): Included these more specific properties just in case, but we might just want to have it go to the broader "has date of manifestation" since we can't tell which property exactly it goes to -MCM 2021-12-15
